2:22 PM; Case called for Plea/sentencing hearing. Prosecuting attorney Andrew Nesheim in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Mitchell A Kraus in court.  Attorney J Andrew Herbers Jr. in court for Mitchell A Kraus.  Victim rights have been complied with by the Waukesha County District Attorneys Office.  Court notes a plea questionnaire has been filed and recites the offer as listed in the document.  Atty. Herbers and the State confirm the offer.  Court conducts plea colloquy with the defendant.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Counts 1 & 2, Court finds defendant guilty. Court will order that cases 20CM2043, 20CT1051, 21CM873 & 22CM245 be dismissed and read into this case.

Sentencing arguments made by the State.
Sentencing arguments made by Atty. Herbers.
Defendant presents statements.

COUNT 1:
The Court Orders the Following:

Withheld sentence

Term of Probation: 1 Year

Conditions of Probation:
-	Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
-	Follow any conditions deemed appropriate by Agent;
-	No contact with Victim A listed in the Criminal Complaint in case 20CM2043.
-	Not operate a motor vehicle without a valid driver's license;
-	Perform 25 Hours of Community Service;
-	Defendant is not to possess any firearms.

RESTITUTION: $1,337.50  to be paid to Victim A; resulting from case 20CM2043 - Court also ordered that this be paid within the first 6 Months of Probation;

COSTS:  $243.00;

DNA Surcharge: $200.00;

DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 

Total costs/fine/forfeiture:  Court to apply the $50.00 Cash Bail on deposit in cases 20CM2043, 20CT1051 & 21CM873; remainder to be paid as a condition of probation. Failure to pay;  will result in a civil judgment.


